Extract a private `fn write_stl_binary(mesh: &Mesh, writer: &mut impl Write) -> Result<usize>` that owns the header/triangle loop. Both `export_stl` and `export_stl_to_fd` become thin wrappers that construct their respective writer and delegate:

```rust
fn write_stl_binary(mesh: &Mesh, writer: &mut impl Write) -> Result<usize> {
    let header = [0u8; 80];
    writer.write_all(&header)?;
    let triangles = mesh.triangles();
    let tri_count = (triangles.len() / 3) as u32;
    writer.write_all(&tri_count.to_le_bytes())?;
    let vertices = mesh.vertices();
    let mut bytes_written: usize = 84;
    for tri in triangles.chunks(3) {
        writer.write_all(&[0u8; 12])?;
        for &idx in tri {
            let v = &vertices[idx as usize];
            writer.write_all(&(v.x as f32).to_le_bytes())?;
            writer.write_all(&(v.y as f32).to_le_bytes())?;
            writer.write_all(&(v.z as f32).to_le_bytes())?;
        }
        writer.write_all(&0u16.to_le_bytes())?;
        bytes_written += 50;
    }
    Ok(bytes_written)
}
```

Use `ManuallyDrop` to prevent the `File` from closing the fd, then call `writer.into_inner()` and wrap that in a `ManuallyDrop<File>` so the fd survives the function:
```rust
use std::mem::ManuallyDrop;
let file = ManuallyDrop::new(unsafe { File::from_raw_fd(fd) });
let mut writer = BufWriter::new(unsafe { File::from_raw_fd(fd) });
// ... write ...
writer.flush()?;
let _ = writer.into_inner(); // flushes BufWriter; inner File::drop is NOT called because we reconstruct from fd
```
Alternatively, use `std::os::unix::io::BorrowedFd` / write via a raw `Write` impl over the borrowed fd (e.g. via `unsafe { &mut *(&mut writer as *mut _) }` pattern, or the `os_pipe` / `nix` crate helpers) so no ownership is taken in the first place.

```rust
for tri in triangles.chunks_exact(3) {
    let mut record = [0u8; 50];
    // normal placeholder already 0
    for (i, &idx) in tri.iter().enumerate() {
        let v = &vertices[idx as usize];
        let base = 12 + i * 12;
        record[base..base+4].copy_from_slice(&(v.x as f32).to_le_bytes());
        record[base+4..base+8].copy_from_slice(&(v.y as f32).to_le_bytes());
        record[base+8..base+12].copy_from_slice(&(v.z as f32).to_le_bytes());
    }
    // attribute bytes already 0
    writer.write_all(&record)?;
    bytes_written += 50;
}
