Prevent File from taking ownership of the fd by wrapping it in ManuallyDrop so the destructor never runs:

```rust
use std::mem::ManuallyDrop;
let mut owned = ManuallyDrop::new(unsafe { File::from_raw_fd(fd) });
let mut writer = BufWriter::new(&mut *owned);
// ... writes ...
writer.flush()?;
// owned is dropped here but ManuallyDrop suppresses File::drop, so fd stays open
```
Alternatively, if the intent is actually to close the fd on return, update the doc comment and remove the contradictory trailing comment, and ensure callers do not attempt to use fd after the call.

